 and Suncorp (Agency: Crooton)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Deloitte Australia, KPMG Australia (Agency: GoodTime)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Careers Service <br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2024 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Queensland University of Technology</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: DeakinTALENT &#8211; Deakin University, RMIT University (Industry &amp; Global Experience), University of South Australia</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Industry Partner </p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2024 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Trellis Collective</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Brightworks, GradConnection, Prosple</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Graduate Program Graduate Intake Under 50</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by graduates participating in the 2024 AAGE Graduate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Pilbara Minerals</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Bankwest, MYOB, SEEK</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Graduate Program (Graduate Intake Over 50)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by graduates participating in the 2024 AAGE Graduate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Atlassian</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Allens, NAB, Qantas</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Internship Program (Intern Intake Under 50)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by interns participating in the 2024 AAGE Intern Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Synergy</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Adobe, Pitcher Partners, RAA</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Internship Program (Intern Intake Over 50)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by interns participating in the 2024 AAGE Intern Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Allens</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Gilbert + Tobin, Herbert Smith Freehills, Macquarie Group Services</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Large Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2025 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Ashley Holihan - Deloitte</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Angelos Zervas - Deloitte, Farah Bayley - GHD, Marissa Simai - EY</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Medium Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2025 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Whitney Spooner - Transgrid</p><p><strong>FINA<span>L</span>ISTS</strong>: Ollie Treloar - Australian National Audit Office, Sue Bentley - Sydney Water, Suzie Moore - Alstom Transport Australia</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Small Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2025 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Kristina Nutt - MYOB</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Gordana Stankovski - Suburban Rail Loop Authority, Ian Tsolakis - Synergy, Sarah Middleton - Qinetiq</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Exhibitor at the AAGE Conference<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by 2024 AAGE Conference Delegates)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: Be Challenged</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Brightworks, GradConnection, Prosple</p></div></div></div></div></td><td><div></div></td><td><div><div><div ><div><p><img src="https://pr-9q32ba.run402.com/_blob/assets/aage/agrias3-373px-e57698cc-efb29902.png" alt="" title="" loading="lazy"><br></p></div></div><div ><div><p><img src="https://pr-9q32ba.run402.com/_blob/assets/aage/agrias1-373px-d997ae39-0580842c.png" alt="" title="" loading="lazy"><br></p></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div></div></div></td></tr></table></div><div ><div><p><br></p></div></div></div></div></div>', false, false, NULL, true);
INSERT INTO pages (slug, title, content, requires_auth, show_in_nav, nav_position, published) VALUES ('2023-agrias-winners', '2023 AGRIAs Winners', '<div><div><div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><h1>Recognising excellence in the early careers industry</h1></div></div><div ><div><a href="/page.html?slug=join-us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join us</a></div></div></div></div></td><td><div></div></td><td></td></tr></table></div></div></div></div><!-- /content zone --><!-- footer zone --><div><div><div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><p>Congratulations to the 2023 AGRIAs winners and finalists!</p></div></div></div></div></td></tr></table></div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Integrated Marketing Campaign (Graduate Intake Under 50) <br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> IMC Trading (Agency: code d&#8217;azur)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> CSL (Agency: Fusion Graduate Consultancy), Department of Planning, Lands and Heritage (WA), Suburban Rail Loop Authority (Agency: Fusion Graduate Consultancy)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Integrated Marketing Campaign (Graduate Intake Over 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER: </strong>Deloitte Australia</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Commonwealth Bank of Australia (Agency: Re), IAG, Westpac Group (Agency: White Space Concepts)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Will Spensley Memorial Award for Innovation in the Graduate Market (Graduate Intake Under 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> IMC Trading (Agency: code d''azur)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: Department of Defence &#8211; Australian Geospatial Intelligence Organisation, Macpherson Kelley</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Will Spensley Memorial Award for Innovation in the Graduate Market (Graduate Intake Over 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Atlassian</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> CyberCX, EY</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Careers Service <br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> UNSW Business School (Career Accelerator)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> RMIT University (College of Business and Law), RMIT University (Industry &amp; Global Experience), University of Wollongong</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Supplier Partner <br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER: </strong>The Career Conversation</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Forage, GradConnection, Prosple</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Industry Association<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>as determined by the 2023 AGRIAs Judging Panel)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Chartered Accountants Australia and New Zealand</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Graduate Program (Graduate Intake Under 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by graduates participating in the 2023 AAGE Graduate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Department of Transport and Planning (VIC)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>carsales.com, Partners in Performance, REA Group</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Graduate Program (Graduate Intake Over 50)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by graduates participating in the 2023 AAGE Graduate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER: </strong>Capgemini</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> Allens, Atlassian, BDO</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Internship Program (Graduate Intake Under 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by interns participating in the 2023 AAGE Intern Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER</strong>: NTT</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>: AustralianSuper, E &amp; P Financial Group, RAA</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Outstanding Internship Program (Graduate Intake Over 50)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by interns participating in the 2023 AAGE Intern Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Atlassian</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Allens, Clayton Utz, King &amp; Wood Mallesons</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Large Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2024 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Ashley Holihan - Deloitte</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Alice Ru - Deloitte, Alyssa Mifsud - Deloitte, Angelos Zervas - Deloitte, Zuli Posada - Atlassian</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Medium Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2024 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Farah Bayley - GHD</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Charlie Cowell - BDO, Jess Saunders - BDO, Jonathon Bowman - Rio Tinto, Sarah McGahen - GHD</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Graduate Recruiter (Small Program)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by candidates participating in the 2024 AAGE Candidate Survey)</p><p><strong>WINNER: </strong>Kristina Nutt - MYOB</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> Hannah Stevenson - QBE Insurance, Melissa McKenzie - Department of Transport and Planning (VIC), Sonja Girazova - Australian Bureau of Statistics, Sue Bentley - Sydney Water</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Exhibitor at the AAGE Conference<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by 2023 AAGE Conference Delegates)</p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> Brightworks</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong> GradConnection, HireVue</p></div></div></div></div></td><td><div></div></td><td><div><div><div ><div><p><img src="https://pr-9q32ba.run402.com/_blob/assets/aage/agrias3-373px-e57698cc-efb29902.png" alt="" title="" loading="lazy"><br></p></div></div><div ><div><p><img src="https://pr-9q32ba.run402.com/_blob/assets/aage/agrias1-373px-d997ae39-0580842c.png" alt="" title="" loading="lazy"><br></p></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div><div ><div></div></div></div></div></td></tr></table></div><div ><div><p><br></p></div></div></div></div></div>', false, false, NULL, true);
INSERT INTO pages (slug, title, content, requires_auth, show_in_nav, nav_position, published) VALUES ('2022-agrias-winners', '2022 AGRIAs Winners', '<div><div><div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><h1>Recognising excellence in the early careers industry</h1></div></div><div ><div><a href="/page.html?slug=join-us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join us</a></div></div></div></div></td><td><div></div></td><td></td></tr></table></div></div></div></div><!-- /content zone --><!-- footer zone --><div><div><div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><p>Congratulations to the 2022 AGRIAs winners and finalists!</p></div></div></div></div></td></tr></table></div><div><table><tr><td><div><div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Integrated Marketing Campaign (Organisations with Graduate Intakes Under 100)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by AAGE employer members participating in the 2022 AGRIAs voting process)<br></p><p><strong>JOINT WINNERs:</strong> IMC Trading (Agency: Noble Agency) &amp; TasNetworks (Agency: the 20)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS:</strong>&nbsp;Evolution Mining &amp; Herbert Smith Freehills (Agency; Noble Agency)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Award for Most Popular Integrated Marketing Campaign (Organisations with Graduate Intakes Over 100)<br></p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by AAGE employer members participating in the 2022 AGRIAs voting process)</p><p><strong>WINNER: </strong>Westpac Group (Agency: White Space Concepts)</p><p><strong>FINALISTS: </strong>Aurecon &amp; Macquarie Group</p></div></div><div ><div><p>Will Spensley Memorial Award for Innovation in the Graduate Market (Graduate Intake Under 100)</p></div></div><div ><div><p>(as determined by AAGE employer members participating in the 2022 AGRIAs voting process)<br></p><p><strong>WINNER:</strong> IMC Trading&nbsp;</p><p><strong>FINALISTS</strong>:&nbsp;MYOB &amp; Unilever Australia </p></div></div><div ><div><p>Will Spensley Memorial Award for Innovation in the Gradua