ubmitted and approved prior to the event. 7. It is the responsibility of the exhibitor to secure appropriate Public Liability Insurance for their organisation in order to particip
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('AAGE AGRIAs Webinar – Inclusive and Accessible Recruitment', 'This is an opportunity to learn directly from other AAGE members who have been recognised by their peers for their initiatives, ask questions, and take away practical ideas to apply in your own recruitment and early careers practices. This webinar will be held as follows: 1.00pm - 2.00pm ACT/NSW/TAS/VIC/QLD time 12.30pm - 1.30pm SA/NT time 11.00am - 12.00 noon WA time You will recei ve a confirmation email upon registering. The AAGE will send a separate email to participants prior to the webinar with the link to join. Enquiries Please contact events@aage.com.au .
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('2026 AAGE Candidate Survey Summary Report Purchase', 'Register Click ''Register'' to purchase the Summary Report The 2026 AAGE Candidate Survey is based on research conducted by the AAGE with over 2,200 responses from candidates joining 100 different organisations in 2026. The AAGE Candidate Survey provides insights into the motivations and perceptions of, and experience with, the 2026 graduate campaign including: Factors which influence application and offer acceptance decisions Experience through the recruitment and selection process The use of artificial intelligence in recruitment and selection processes Discernment around offer acceptance and the reasons why candidates renege An understanding of ideal working arrangements. Published annually, this research has become an invaluable resource for industry professionals. For 19 years, the AAGE Candidate Survey has been highlighting key trends and insights within the early career sector. The survey gathers comprehensive feedback from candidates across a range organisations across industry groups. The robust and independent data set along with the insights shared enable employers to benchmark the experience of their recruitment and selection process and strategically plan their future graduate recruitment efforts. Members who participate in the research receive a complimentary digital copy of the report and other members can purchase the highly informative Summary Report at a special discounted rate. Members must log into their profile to access the member rate. Please contact surveys@aage.com.au with any queries.
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('2026 AAGE Employer Survey Summary Report Purchase', 'Register Click ''Register'' to purchase the Summary Report The 2026 AAGE Employer Survey is based on research conducted by the AAGE with 153  different organisations taking part. The AAGE Employer Survey provides the latest information on: Vacancy levels and application numbers for graduate roles commencing in 2026 Salary levels for new graduates starting work in 2026 Selection processes used by recruiters in 2025 Spend on marketing, selection and development activities in 2025 Graduate program management and retention Industry challenges. Released each year, this study was the first of its kind to be made commercially available. Outlining some important and interesting trends in our growing industry, the survey captures responses from various industry organisations, providing ways for members to benchmark themselves against their competitors and help them to plan for upcoming graduate recruitment campaigns. Members have access to a discounted price and members who participate receive a complimentary soft copy of the report. Members must log into their profile to access the member rate. Please contact surveys@aage.com.au with any queries.
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('2026 AAGE Graduate Survey Summary Report Purchase', 'Register Click ''Register'' to purchase the Summary Report The 2026 AAGE Graduate Survey aims to understand graduates’ perceptions and experiences of their first year of employment by having participants rate their employer across a range of criteria including access to learning and development, quality of work and assessment of program features. The Summary Report is based on this research with over 3,200 responses from the 2025 intake of graduates across over 180 organisations and provides comprehensive insights, highlighting key trends and presenting recommendations. To allow for the observation of trends over time, data from the 2025 Graduate Survey has also been included. The report also includes comparisons to the results from the Top 15 employers, made up of the top five employers from the three program sizes of small (intake less than 20), medium (intake of 21-70) or large (intake of 71 or more). The Top 25 employers in each category with the highest overall average ratings are listed on the Top Graduate Employers website. We believe these insights will help employers to evaluate their organisation and gain a better understanding of industry best practices. Members must log into their profile to access the member rate. Please contact surveys@aage.com.au with any queries.
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('2025 AAGE Intern Survey Insights Report Purchase', 'Register'' to purchase the Insights Report The 2025 AAGE Intern Survey is based on research conducted by the AAGE, with over 2,500 responses from students across 127 organisations who have completed an internship over the March 2024 to February 2025 period. The survey provides the latest market information on: Reasons behind internship search and an assessment of the channels used and valued Insight into the decision-making process behind internship selection as well as internship to graduate conversion Ratings of internships across organisational experience, interaction with colleagues and professional development opportunities. Year after year, employers have found the survey to be an invaluable resource. It enables them to compare their performance with industry best practices and strategically prepare for future campaigns. Members must log into their profile to access the member rate. Please contact surveys@aage.com.au with any queries.
INSERT INTO events (title, description, location, starts_at, ends_at, capacity, image_url, is_members_only, created_by) VALUES ('The AAGE ''How To'' Handbook: A guide to graduate recruitment', 'The AAGE ''How To'' Handbook: A guide to graduate recruitment When 31 Dec 2026 Location Soft copy only - Link sent via email Registration Member Rate – $20.00 Standard (Non-Member) Rate – $40.00 Register Click ''Register'' to purchase the handbook The AAGE ''How To'' Handbook: A guide to graduate recruitment has been produced by the Australian Association of Graduate Employers Ltd (AAGE). A subcommittee of graduate recruitment industry veterans, whose careers have been dedicated to the recruitment and development of graduates, have shared and combined their experience and ideas, giving rise to this publication. The handbook is designed to assist those new to the industry, as well as serve those who are already involved in graduate recruitment to seek best practice. Topics include the attraction, selection, induction and development of graduates, and content is included regarding professional development for graduate employers themselves. Members must log into their profile to access the member rate. Please contact info@aage.com.au with any queries.
INSERT INTO announcements (title, body, is_pinned, author_id) VALUES ('AAGE public site port','This Kychon portal was generated from public AAGE website content on 2026-05-04. Member-only/admin data was not scraped.',true,(SELECT id FROM members WHERE email='info@aage.com.au'));
